Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> How easy is it REALLY to get the Book of Souls solo?</span><hr size=1> Well I've been wanting to go to Hate solo to get my book of souls, but when I've talked to the wizards who I asked to port me up and a few different rogues, they said they didn't think it was worth the risk to do it solo.  Honestly, I don't have the resources to put together a full-fledged raid, and who knows how long it will take to wait for one of my friends' guilds to plan one.  <br>
<br>
So what is your honest opinion...it sounded somewhat simple to me, just avoid the liches, con stuff, hide/sneak...but maybe it's more difficult than I think?  Any advice would be appreciated! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxetrintheblackguard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xetrin the Blackguard</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/3/02 11:59:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15591.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How easy is it REALLY to get the Book of Souls solo?</span><hr size=1> Personally, I wouldn't wanna take the chance if I were you.  You can, and will most likely make it, but depending on your luck, you might aggro     , die, not get ressed(most likely), and still not get the book, so I'd say don't bother.  However, if you've got the exp to spare the chance, and just can't find a single raid willing to let you pay your way and loot it, then by all means, take the risk. <p><hr>
