Take a chance.  Go up naked and all you'll lose is exp if the worst happens.  I can't tell you how fun it is, especially if it's your first time to Hate.  It's like a real horror movie. <p><html><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=234198>Pualani</a><br>Rake, <a href=http://www30.brinkster.com/djseng/SotO>Scream of the Owl</a><br>Torvonnilous<html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usabyn85.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sabyn85</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/4/02 4:23:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15591.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How easy is it REALLY to get the Book of Souls solo?</span><hr size=1> I did it when I was lvl 52 and it is fairly simple if you have a map and you have been to hate before. The first time I went, I invised before I gated with a wiz then I sneak/hide but I forgot to turn off invis so an abhorrent saw me and I used a Merchant made insta-cast gate potion. The second time I went, I got lost and ended up near Maestro. He personally came down and beat me to death with my own shoes. The third time I went, I did it flawlessly. It's a real rush when you get it and I'd say it's definately worth a shot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uparticleboy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>particleboy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/4/02 4:54:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15591.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How easy is it REALLY to get the Book of Souls solo?</span><hr size=1> Wouldn't risk it?  Bah!  It should be the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> only</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> way to do it.  Picking it up whena  raid clear the level is kinda cheesy.  If you buy an instant gate potion and a hatestone it'll cost you about 1300 plat and 5-10 minutes of time for you and a wizard.  The worst that can happen is you lose your money, don't get the book and have to eat a death (this last one shouldn't happen since you have a gate potion but maybe you go LD or something).  And all thats unlikely to happen if you're careful and follow the guide. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=163097">Hagin Netherblade</a><br>
Barbarian Assassin of <a href="http://www.thunder.at">Thunder</a><br>
Innoruuk Server
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucindermage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cinder Mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/4/02 7:36:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15591.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How easy is it REALLY to get the Book of Souls solo?</span><hr size=1> <br>
It's worth the risk. It's not THAT hard, if you're patient. If the south route is blocked, you can always go north and cut across the middle of the zone and vice versa. Go camp a CT gate potion, you can sneak/hide out of CT from the maze without being seen. It costs you nothing, there's no risk of dying in Hate with it, and the thrill of being up there is the highlight of the epic quest in my opinion. <p><center>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65334 > Maxs Powwer </a>
</br>
57th Dwarven Blackguard </br>
New Dawn Rising</br>
<i>"I don't get mad, I get stabby" </i>
</center>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzylc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zylc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/4/02 7:48:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15591.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How easy is it REALLY to get the Book of Souls solo?</span><hr size=1> Dude!  Don't stress. Once you do it, you're going to laugh about how easy it was.<br>
<br>
Grab a map, a quick way to get out (Gate Potion or rez), and go. There was a very map that I used that was posted around here several times.  It shows where the Lich Patrol Routes are (the mobs that see through invis) and exactly how to get to the Book of Souls.  Scroll down a bit, and look at the other forums involving the Book of Souls.<br>
<br>
The run through Hate is a cakewalk just as long as you know the Lich Patrol Routes.  It FREAKS YOU OUT, I know, thinking about doing this alone -- I was scared.  It was the only one in the zone when doing my run. It's a rush. =P    But it's VERY easy to do solo; there's no need for a raid -- the Book is in the Maestro room, on the upper floor...Which is pretty deep inside Hate.<br>
<br>
The Book is NO DROP -- unless it's MQ'able, so you're going to have to do it yourself, anyway.<br>
